<div class="courseblock main">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>REES&#160;20004.  Nabokov:  Lolita.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
Lolita, light of my life, fire of my loins. My sin, my soul, Lolita: the tip of the tongue taking a trip of three steps down the palate, to tap at three on the teeth." Popular as Nabokov's "all-American" novel is, it is rarely discussed beyond its psychosexual profile. This intensive text-centered and discussion-based course attempts to supersede the univocal obsession with the novel's pedophiliac plot as such by concerning itself above all with the novel's language: language as failure, as mania, and as conjuration.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): M. Sternstein&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Terms Offered: Autumn<br />
Equivalent Course(s): ENGL 28916, SIGN 26027, FNDL 25300, GNSE 24900<br />
</p>
