<div class="courseblock main">
<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>REES&#160;26603.  Soviet Cinema and the Avant-Garde.  100 Units.</strong></p><p class="courseblockdesc">
This course examines some of the most ambitious claims about what cinema as a medium can do by early Soviet filmmakers. We look at the extraordinary flourishing of cinema in the Soviet Union in the 1920s and 30s including films by Eisenstein, Vertov, Shub, Pudovkin and Dovzhenko, their theoretical writings, their collaborations with avant-garde artists and theater designers, and their far-reaching influence on film and film theory. We will also consider the political and historical context of the films and their creators.</p><p class="courseblockdetail">
Instructor(s): Anne E. Moss&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Terms Offered: Winter<br />
Equivalent Course(s): REES 36603, CMST 24507<br />
